<font color="#FF0000">ON LANDMINES</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct 24 13:44:38 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
We are kidding ourselves if we ever think that there will be a multi-lateral eradication of landmine warfare.<br><br>
Ed Ramon made a good point in one of his first posts to this site concerning The Rules Of Engagement. To paraphrase: rules are ok when  agreed to by factions who ARE in agreement. Warring factions, if they had the wherewithal to agree, wouldn't be at war.<br><br>
As an infantryman in Americal in 1970, I had the experience of setting out mechanical ambushes using claymores connected to batteries with trip wires - which were in violation of the Geneva Convention. <br><br>
So who is kidding who? They can outlaw anything they want, but if landmines or germs or chemicals will &quot;carry the day&quot;, no particular faction is going to give a shit if anything they do is against the rules.<br><br>
I am not usually this negative, as I'm sure that Princess Diana was sincere in her efforts. All's fair in love and war, sorry.<br><br>
Maybe 'twould be better (and easier) to not have the damned wars in the first place.
